□ No promises or guarantees on management's behalf beyond what they stated

9. TEMPORAL LOGIC
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
□ DATES: For any sentence with 2+ dates, verify chronological order
  - List all dates in the sentence
  - Verify earlier date comes before later date
  - Example WRONG: "Price $50 on Nov 15, fell to $45 by Nov 10" (backwards time)
  - Example CORRECT: "Price $45 on Nov 10, rose to $50 by Nov 15"
  - If sequence unclear or dates conflict: Use range format or single most recent date
□ Q&A progression accurately reflects order of questions
□ Guidance periods correctly sequenced (Q4 before FY, FY 2024 before FY 2025)

10. UNIT CONSISTENCY
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
